      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "SAT English questions usually come with a short 1-2 paragraph passage, followed by a question about the passage.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The questions are always multiple choice, with 4 options to choose from.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "SAT English tests mainly test the following:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Grammar and Punctuation",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Vocabulary",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice completes the text with the most logical and precise word or phrase?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Reading Comprehension",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "items" : [
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "According to the text, (question about the text’s contents)",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "What is the main idea of the text?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Which choice best states the main purpose of the text?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice best supports the author’s argument?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice most logically completes the text?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice best describes the overall structure of the text?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice most effectively uses relevant information from the XXX to accomplish this goal",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice most effectively uses data from the graph to complete the example",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "⭐ Which choice best describes the function of the underlined sentence in the text as a whole?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "content" : [
                        {
                          "inlineContent" : [
                            {
                              "text" : "Based on the texts, what would the author of Text 2 most likely say about Text 1?",
                              "type" : "text"
                            }
                          ],
                          "type" : "paragraph"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "unorderedList"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Strategy",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Strategy",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Some general purpose strategies to answering questions",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Weighing-Answers",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Weighing Answers",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Don’t weigh your answers “pros” against each other (“A fits, but B also fits”). Insted, focus on the “cons” of each answer.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Two answers might both fit, but one might have a small detail that doesn’t fit, such as stating something that the text does",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "not actually say.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Annotations",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Annotations",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "As of the time of writing, there are two annotation tools: highlights and notes. Highlights give you three different colours.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Unlike a lot of SAT suggestions, I’d suggest NOT using annotations unless you’re stuck on a question (and have come back",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to it after solving the easy ones). Annotations take a lot of time to type, which is better spent on solving other simple",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "questions.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "I’d recommend using highlighters to highlight IMPORTANT parts of a passage or question. Unimportant parts stay",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "unhighlighted. Use different colours so that you can differentiate between different types of important parts.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Grammar",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Grammar",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Grammar usually tests these three:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Plurality (of both nouns and verbs)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Tense (past, present, future, infinitive\/none)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Punctuation (commas, semicolons, colons, dashes)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Plurality",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Plurality",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For some reason, if the noun is a plural, the verb is a singular. If the noun is singular, the verb is plural.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "For example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The dog ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "(singular)",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " barks ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "(singular)",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The dogs ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "(plural)",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " bark ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "(plural)",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The SAT will try to hide this, possibly by adding stuff in brackets or making the sentence very long. It is your",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "job to identify which noun is the subject of the sentence, and pluralise the verb accordingly. For example, a term",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "like “shape of ears” is SINGULAR, because the subject is “shape”, not “ears”.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Punctuation",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Punctuation",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "In general: Dashes are interchangable with commas, semicolons (”;”) are interchangable with periods, and colons indicate",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "an example or list.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "One thing that the SAT likes to do is test where you’d put a colon with regards to a connecting word. For example:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "“Alice knows hundreds of dog breeds. Only three of these dogs are included in her _____ A, B, C, D, and E - of which is grouped with the other dogs despite not being a domesticated dog breed.”",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Connections should be used whenever two parts of a sentence are not directly related to each other, for example, this sentence.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Usually, you are taught to include the connecting word (eg. “however”) with the sentence after the connector. But in this",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "special case, the “however” has NOTHING to do with the succeeding sentence, so it goes BEFORE the colon (“book, however:”)",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Semicolons",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Semicolons",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Semicolons are used in these two situations:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "A list where individual items have commas in them or are very long",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "To join together two related statements, where both statements could be their own sentence",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Apostrophe",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Apostrophe",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Apostrophes are used to indicate possession. There are three general exceptions to the “’s indicates posession” rule:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "If the subject is a plural that ends with an “s”, the apostrophe goes AFTER the “s”",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "If the subject is “it”, the possessive form is “its” (no apostrophe), and the expansion “it is” has an apostrophe",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Other than those two cases, “’s” ALWAYS indicates possession.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Vocabulary",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Vocabulary",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Fill-the-blank questions are usually the hardest, as they require you to know the meaning of a word in a specific context.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "These types of questions usually fall under one of these categories:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Contrasting with other specific terms. These fit into sentences like “A tends to be X, wheras B tends to be BLANK” or vice versa. The word",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "you choose for BLANK should contrast with X. Note that contrasting sentences can be VERY sneaky, since the contrasting term (usually “but”) might come",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "at the start of the sentence instead of the middle.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Complementing with other specific terms. These usually fit into sentences like “A tends to be like X, similarly, B tends to be BLANK” or vice versa.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "The word should be similar to X. These types of questions are more advanced than they seem, since it can actually occur within a contrast-looking",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "question that is involves a double negative, making it a complementing question.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Describing the next sentence. These fit into sentence pairs, where the first sentene (where the BLANK is) tends to be a statement",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "and the next sentence tends to be an elaboration. They usually require you to identify the ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "purpose",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " of the elaboration. For example, if the elaboration",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "sentence talks about accuracy of a method, the BLANK might be “precise”\/“accurate”\/another synonym.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Relating to the previous sentence. These are similar to the previous type, except that the BLANK is within the explanation. They usually",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "require you to identify the ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "subject matter",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " of the statement. For example, if the statement talks about a flare, the BLANK might have to do",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "with its location or brightness.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Theres also a different variant of this question, that goes something like “what does the underlined word mean?”. These",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "can also be treated as fill-the-blank questions, just treat each of the explanation phrases as a candidate word.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
